HEADWORD: Peziza
<hw>Pe*zi"za</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
corrupt. from L. <ets>pezica</ets> a sessile mushroom, fr. Gr.
<grk>pe`zis</grk>, fr. <grk>pe`za</grk>, <grk>poy`s</grk>, a
foot.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of fungi embracing a great
